Creating a Maven Project with eclipse: These are the following steps...

Step 1> To create a maven project, choose the directory to store the project directory and run the below command in the 
        terminal.

Cmd> mvn3 archetype:generate -DgroupId=com.naga -DartifcatId=NumberGenerator 
-DarchetypeArtifactId=maven-archetype-quickstart -DinteractiveMode=false

The above command will create the project directory structure in the current directory..

.
|-- pom.xml
`-- src
    |-- main
    |   `-- java
    |       `-- com
    |           `-- naga
    |               `-- App.java
    `-- test
        `-- java
            `-- com
                `-- naga
                    `-- AppTest.java


Step 2> To enable this project in Eclipse IDE, run the following command in termonal

Cmd> mvn3 eclipse:eclipse

Step 3> Import the project into Eclipse.

        File --> Import --> General --> Existing projects into workspace
        
Step 4> Write the application logic and save

Step 5> Compile and package by using the following command

Cmd> mvn3 package
